TITLE.0: ACE> Solar Wind Ion Composition Spectrometer 1.1

LINK_TEXT.0: Release notes and other info available at

LINK_TITLE.0: the ACE Science Center  Level 2 Data website

TEXT.0: SWICS 1.1 - The Solar Wind Ion Composition Spectrometer prior to August 23 2011 -

TEXT.1: determines uniquely the chemical and ionic-charge composition of the solar wind,

TEXT.2: the temperatures and mean speeds of major solar wind ions, at all speeds

TEXT.3: above 300 km/s (protons) and 170 km/s  (Fe+16), and resolves H and He isotopes

TEXT.4: of solar and interstellar sources. SWICS 1.1 measures the distribution functions

TEXT.5: of the interstellar cloud and dust cloud pickup ions up to energies of 100 keV/e.

TEXT.6: For more information about the SWICS instrument, visit the SWICS Home Page at

TEXT.8: The quality of ACE level 2 data is such that it is suitable for serious

TEXT.9: scientific study.  However, to avoid confusion and misunderstanding, it

TEXT.10: is recommended that users consult with the appropriate ACE team members

TEXT.11: before publishing work derived from the data. The ACE team has worked

TEXT.12: hard to ensure that the level 2 data are free from errors, but the team

TEXT.13: cannot accept responsibility for erroneous data, or for misunderstandings

TEXT.14: about how the data may be used. This is especially true if the appropriate

TEXT.15: ACE team members are not consulted before publication. At the very

TEXT.16: least, preprints should be forwarded to the ACE team before publication.

Rules_of_use.0: See the rules of use available from the ACE
